  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reduce unorganized commercial exploitation / illicit trafficking and encourage research for underwater heritage</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Underwater cultural heritage is threatened by a number of different factors - among several issues, the looting and commercial recovery of underwater cultural heritage and the destruction of their context are the most prominent challenges. 

As a long-term strategy to encourage the countries under JAK cluster to ratify both the 1970 and 2001 Conventions, CLT/JAK proposes to allocate its resources on the following activities: 

&#x2022;	Reconciliation of the national regulations with UNESCO 1970 and 2001 Conventions 
&#x2022;	Sensitization and training of stakeholders, in particular police and coast guard forces to protect UCH sites;
&#x2022;	Assistance to maritime museum and research development;
&#x2022;	Exchange of good field projects</narrative>
  </description>
